y. The module includes a `getAdminSummary` function to fetch summary data. I need to integrate the `DashboardResponse`'s structure with my broader API flow now.\n\n```text\nI'm now defining the structure of the `dashboard` module. I've created the `DashboardSummary` and `DashboardResponse` interfaces for type safety. The module includes a `getAdminSummary` function to fetch summary data. I need to integrate the `DashboardResponse`'s structure with my broader API flow now.\n```\n\n**Implementing Client Module**\n\nI'm now implementing the `clients` module, focusing on handling standard requests such as `GET /clients` and `GET /clients/:id`. I've added a mock fallback array for graceful data handling in case the backend is unavailable. I'm leveraging existing mocks from `app/api/v1/dashboard/admin/route.ts` to improve testing. I'm now testing.\n\n\n**Defining Client Types**\n\nI'm now defining the structure for the client module's data. I've designed `ClientAccount`, `ClientsListResponse`, and `ClientDetailResponse` interfaces. My plan is to include a mock fallback to address any lack of backend routes. I'm focusing on defining functions to handle client data requests.\n\n\n**Implementing User Module**\n\nI'm now implementing the `users` module, and I am incorporating a mock fallback to match any missing backend routes. This strategy uses data derived from my recent client module, as well. I'm focusing on GET, POST, PATCH requests using the API's supported queries and body parameters, while still using error handling and client-safe coding practices.\n\n\n"}}
